<item>
            <title>[SPARK-5479] PySpark on yarn mode need to support non-local python files</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-5479</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt; In &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-5162&quot; title=&quot;Python yarn-cluster mode&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-5162&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-5162&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=vgrigor&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;vgrigor&quot;&gt;vgrigor&lt;/a&gt; reports this:&lt;br/&gt;
Now following code cannot work:&lt;br/&gt;
aws emr add-steps --cluster-id &quot;j-XYWIXMD234&quot; \&lt;br/&gt;
--steps Name=SparkPi,Jar=s3://eu-west-1.elasticmapreduce/libs/script-runner/script-runner.jar,Args=&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;/home/hadoop/spark/bin/spark-submit,--deploy-mode,cluster,--master,yarn-cluster,--py-files,s3://mybucketat.amazonaws.com/tasks/main.py,main.py,param1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;,ActionOnFailure=CONTINUE&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;so we need to support non-local python files on yarn client and cluster mode.&lt;br/&gt;
before submitting application to Yarn, we need to download non-local files to local or hdfs path.&lt;br/&gt;
or spark.yarn.dist.files need to support other non-local files.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
